Changes to traffic conditions, including lane and shoulder closures, will be in place at various times along the Princes Hwy and other nearby roads as a result of the Jervis Bay intersection upgrade project. 

Motorists are advised to allow approximately 5 minutes of additional travel time when traffic control is active.

Full road closure of Jervis Bay Road will be in place on Mon 26 Aug, Tues 27 Aug & Thur 29 Aug. A contraflow will be in place on the Princes Hwy on Thur 29 Aug.

OSOM access will be maintained on the Princes Highway during these closures. OSOM vehicles are to park in designated bays and contact traffic control by UHF channel 28.
Contraflow traffic conditions will be in place to allow motorists to pass in both directions.
Lane closures may be in place during work hours but at least one lane will be maintained in each direction. Some lane closures are in conjunction with the Warringah Freeway Upgrade work.
